# Development Conventions

## Code Style & Patterns

### Import Patterns
- Use path mapping: `import { supabase } from '@/lib/supabase'`
- Keep client configurations in `/lib` directory

### Next.js Patterns
- Use App Router (Next.js 14) by default
- Server components by default unless client interaction required
- Place pages in `src/app/` directory following the routing structure

### Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS for all styling
- Follow utility-first approach
- Maintain consistent spacing and color schemes

### File Organization
- Scaffold files live in `project/` subdirectory
- New features should build on top of existing scaffold
- Do not recreate or overwrite scaffold files unless fixing specific issues

## Database Conventions
- Use Supabase/PostgreSQL for data persistence
- Follow the defined data models (User, Entry, MoodLog)
- Implement Row Level Security (RLS) for user data protection

## API Conventions
- Use Supabase client for database operations
- OpenAI client for AI-generated insights
- Stripe client for payment processing
- Handle errors gracefully with proper user feedback

## Authentication
- Implement Supabase Auth (to be configured)
- Protect routes that require authentication
- Handle authentication state properly across the app

## Feature Development
When building new features, ensure:
- User limits are enforced (5 entries/day, 3 mood logs/day for free tier)
- AI features are properly gated behind payment
- Search functionality works across entries and tags
- Timeline view integrates both entries and mood logs